 0280:             # update gold label feature weights
 0281: 
 0282:             # FOR NOW, we assume no features are shared between classes.
 0283:             # Otherwise we may have to ensure the learner isn't penalizing features that
 0284:             # should fire for both the gold and predicted classes.
 0285: 
 0286:             '''
 0287:             AdaGrad update chooses a different step size for each parameter.
 0288:             Green et al. 2013, eqs. (4) and (5):
 0289:             With respect to a single parameter (component) j:
 0290:                 g_t = gradient w.r.t. j of the loss under the current weight vector
 0291:                 G_t = G_{t-1} + math.pow(g_t, 2)    # i.e., G_t is the sum of squared gradients for this feature until now
 0292:                 w_t = w_{t-1} - η * math.pow(G_t, -0.5) * g_t
 0293:             We fix η = 1.
 0294:             '''

+0658:     def decode(self, nLabels, currentWeights, includeLossTerm, costAugVal, useBIO):
/* Python wrapper */
